    "body": "Looks very nice overall!\r\n\r\nI definitely prefer the microblog format over the chat bubbles. As for suggestions, in right-most screen in [this comment](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/11137#issuecomment-694908392), it intuitively feels a bit off to repeat `carmen.eth 0x0276...` twice while only displaying the profile picture once. I would say I generally prefer the Discord way of solving this problem. They either merge the messages together, all under a single instance of the username and profile picture, or it gets split up and they repeat the username & profile picture.\r\n\r\nAlso, if it's the same person, and the updates were sent in quick succession (in this case it's 59s and 1 minute), then there should probably only be one timestamp.",
